text: Dunne Foxe Island is one of the Canadian arctic islands in Nunavut, Canada within western Hudson Bay. The hamlet of Whale Cove is to the west. The island was named on July 30, 1631 by Arctic explorer, Captain Luke Foxe. ==References== Category:Islands of Hudson Bay Category:Uninhabited islands of Kivalliq Region Category:Islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago
